HEADWORD: Physiophyly
<hw>Phys`i*oph"y*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fy`sis</grk> nature + <?/ a clan.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>The tribal history of the functions, or the history of the
paleontological development of vital activities, -- being a branch of
<branchof>phylogeny</branchof>. See <er>Morphophyly</er>.</def>
<rj><au>Haeckel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

